	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Instead of nesasm, try asm6 (if you want single-pass assembly) or cc65 (if you want a traditional assemble-then-link cycle).
<br />
<br />First you'll need to learn something about the NES architecture. See <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/" class="postlink">our wiki</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


